Darkangel finds Bloodblade and decides to take this bot with him. Angel carefully picks up the injured bot and takes off, in bot mode, for the Tripred base.


Nic &lt;Proudwing500k@...&gt; wrote:
Bloodblade had survived entry, but he was awfully damaged. His armor 
was charred and stripped away at some places, and molten at others. 
He was in definite need for CR.

--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, Richard Allen &lt;roborick007@y...&gt; wrote:
&gt; : : Darkangel : :
&gt; 
&gt; While in flight, returning to the Tripredacus base, Darkangel saw 
Bloodblade come down. He alters course, landing at the touch down 
spot, in bot mode.
&gt; 
&gt; Darkangel: That looked like a bot that went down, not a ship. How 
could any being survive the atmospheric entry?
&gt; 
&gt; Nic &lt;Proudwing500k@h...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Bloodblade, orbiting Earth disguised as a pod, got a confirmation 
&gt; that Rockseeker and Lunekill were both terminated. Reluctantly, he 
&gt; decided to warn his Master.
&gt; 
&gt; Bloodblade: Master Unicron, Rockseeeker and Lunekill have just been 
&gt; terminated.
&gt; 
&gt; The response was immediate and terrible. He was attacked both in 
his 
&gt; body and in his spark, even though his Lord was at the other end of 
&gt; the system. Tendrils of electricity shook him, causing 
interferences 
&gt; that could be picked up from Earth.
&gt; 
&gt; In the middle of his agony, he heard a thundrous voice inside his 
&gt; head.
&gt; 
&gt; Unicron: Incompetent Minions! They have failed me. Now, Bloodblade, 
&gt; it is your turn to go, but I have learned from this.
&gt; 
&gt; When the pain stopped, he had forgotten who he was or who he 
served. 
&gt; He only remembered his name. He started spinning wildly as he 
entered 
&gt; high orbit and was attracted to the ground.
&gt; 
&gt; A few minutes later, he crashed loudly into the ground, exactly at 
&gt; the same distance from the three bases.
